Heritage Oil Rejects 1.2 Billion-Pound Offer, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-17T01:08:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/heritage-oil-rejects-1-2-billion-pound-offer-ft-reports.html
  Heritage Oil Plc (HOIL)  turned down an
informal bid from an unidentified Abu Dhabi-based company which
offered to pay 425 pence a share, valuing Heritage Oil at 1.2
billion pounds ($1.9 billion,) the Financial Times reported,
citing a person familiar with the situation. Heritage rejected
the offer as being too low, the FT reported. The oil and gas
explorer declined to comment, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 